      "body": "**Run 0010 T12 reconcile (session 0088-horizon-T12): PASS \u2014 `Grassmannian.representable` is now a real proof modulo two clean descent leaves.**\n\nVerified against the working tree, not just the report:\n\n- **Lean:** new `Picard/GrassmannianRepresentability.lean` (661 LOC). The old skeleton quantified over an *arbitrary* module `V`; the session corrected the statement to the `[Nitsure]` hypotheses (`V` locally free of rank `r`, `1 \u2264 d \u2264 r`, `Scheme.{0}`) and proved `Grassmannian.representable` from two leaves. Building blocks `representable_of_iso_free` and `representable_restrict` are **axiom-clean** `[propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]`; `representable` carries only `sorryAx` (the two leaves). No hidden top-level sorry.\n- **Leaves (2, both true, general-purpose):** `Scheme.representable_of_openCover` (Zariski descent of representability) and `Grassmannian.isZariskiSheaf` (Zariski sheaf axiom). The descent leaf will be reused for the Quot and Pic endgames.\n- **Build:** representative `lake build` of `GrassmannianRepresentability` + `QuotFunctorDef` is **green** (8592 jobs, exit 0); sorry warnings are exactly the declared leaves (2 here, 5 in `QuotFunctorDef`).\n- **Blueprint honest:** four new nodes with complete paper proofs; `thm:grassmannian_representable` carries statement-`\\leanok` with no proof-`\\leanok`, its `\\uses` edges all resolve. No new dangling.\n- **Hygiene:** working tree clean; `RationalCurveIso.*` scratch removed.\n\nSupersedes the prior-pass note `I-0117` (session 0084). The one open trap on this leg is `QuotScheme` (`I-0118`).",
