      "body": "**Run 0010 T12 reconcile (session 0084-horizon-T12): PASS \u2014 Quot/Grassmannian headline definitions are real.**\n\nVerified end-to-end against the working tree, not just the report:\n\n- **Lean:** new `Picard/QuotFunctorDef.lean` (849 lines) gives real `Scheme.QuotFunctor` (Setoid quotient of quotient-families; morphism action = pullback along `id_X \u00d7_S \u03c8`) and `Scheme.Grassmannian` (rank-`d` locally-free quotients). Representative `lake build` of `QuotFunctorDef` + `QuotScheme` is **green** (8589 jobs, exit 0).\n- **Sorries:** `QuotFunctorDef.lean` has **6** honest typed leaves (3 base-change lemmas `CoherentSheafFlat/HasProperSupport.of_isPullback`, `hilbertFunction_quotBaseMap`; the bookkeeping `pullbackSlicePresentation_isFinite`; and the two endgames `Grassmannian.representable`, `QuotScheme`). `QuotScheme.lean` dropped 7 \u2192 **3** (FBC-gated base-change leaves).\n- **Blueprint honest:** `def:quot_functor`/`def:grassmannian_scheme` carry statement-`\\leanok`. The four `sec:quot_base_change` lemma nodes carry statement-`\\leanok` (signatures are formalized) with **no proof-`\\leanok`** (proofs are sorry) \u2014 correct per convention. No false pins found; parses clean, 0 dangling.\n- **Hygiene:** no stray scratch files; the old `RationalCurveIso.*` scratch files are cleaned up. `AJC.picrep` roadmap comment logs the advance; item stays **active**.\n\n**Next headline:** `Grassmannian.representable` (glue the merged sorry-free absolute `Grassmannian.represents` over a trivialising cover) is the most tractable remaining target.",
